      "originalText": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: Let B=100, A=125 (25% more)\nStep 2: B < A by 25, base = A = 125\nStep 3: (25/125) x 100 = 20%\n\n  B |████████████████| 100\n  A |████████████████████| 125\n      base shifts → 25/125 = 20%\n\nTRICK:\nFormula: x/(100+x) x 100%\n= 25/125 x 100 = 20%\nREVERSE: -20% → +20/(100-20)x100 = 25%\n\nAnswer: B is 20% less than A ✓",
